article.description: Blake Dietrick had 23 points, eight assists and five rebounds as No. 16 Princeton women beat Harvard 78-57 to remain the only undefeated team in women's Division I basketball.
article.headline: No. 16 Princeton beats Harvard, remains only undefeated in women's D-I
article.story:
PRINCETON, N.J. -- Blake Dietrick had 23 points, eight assists and five rebounds as the No. 16 Princeton women beat Harvard 78-57 to remain the only undefeated team in women's Division I basketball.

Annie Tarakchian added 17 points and 14 rebounds for the Tigers (25-0, 9-0 Ivy), who moved within one win of the program record for most in a season (26 in 2009-10).

After Harvard (10-14, 3-7) scored the first four points of the second half to pull within five, Princeton answered with a 12-4 run and steadily pulled away. The Tigers had their largest lead of 23 points just before Harvard capped the scoring with a pair of free throws.

Princeton opened the game 4 of 20 from the field while Harvard took a 15-9 lead with 8:54 to go. The Tigers closed the first half on a 19-4 run.

AnnMarie Healy and Temi Fagbenle led the Crimson with 18 points each.
